Section 1:
Act 354 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/10/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1601
4
5 By: Representatives L. Johnson, McGruder
6 By: Senator J. Dotson
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT REGARDING HIGHER EDUCATION; TO REQUIRE STATE-
10 SUPPORTED INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION TO PROVIDE
11 CAREER COUNSELING AND OTHER RESOURCES TO CERTAIN
12 STUDENTS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO REQUIRE STATE-SUPPORTED INSTITUTIONS
17 OF HIGHER EDUCATION TO PROVIDE CAREER
18 COUNSELING AND OTHER RESOURCES TO
19 CERTAIN STUDENTS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 60, Subchapter 1, is amended
24 to add an additional section to read as follows:
25 6-60-123. Requirement for career counseling and other career-related
26 resources — Definition.
27 (a) As used in this section, "career-related resources" includes
28 without limitation information about:
29 (1) Available career and technical training; and
30 (2) Trade industries that provide employment opportunities.
31 (b) The Division of Higher Education shall maintain an accessible
32 location on its website with a link for career counseling and other career-
33 related resources that are available to students and provided by state-
34 supported institutions of higher education.
35 (c) A state-supported institution of higher education shall:
36 (1) Maintain on its website a link to the division's career
*CRH143*
03-10-2025 11:41:25 CRH143
As Engrossed: H3/10/25 HB1601
1 counseling and other career-related resources available to students; and
2 (2) Take appropriate steps to inform students of career
3 counseling and other career-related resources, including without limitation
4 how to access the information at the state-supported institution of higher
5 education and from the division.
6 (d) The career counseling and other career-related services offered by
7 a state-supported institution of higher education shall remain available to a
8 student who has not yet graduated for up to six (6) months after the student
9 is no longer enrolled at the state-supported institution of higher education,
10 upon request.
11 (e) This section does not apply to a concurrently enrolled student or
12 a student who has enrolled at a subsequent institution of higher education.
13
14 /s/L. Johnson
