Subtitle
15
16 TO REQUIRE STATE-SUPPORTED INSTITUTIONS
17 OF HIGHER EDUCATION TO PROVIDE CAREER
18 COUNSELING AND OTHER RESOURCES TO
19 CERTAIN STUDENTS.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
22
23 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 60, Subchapter 1, is amended
24 to add an additional section to read as follows:
25 6-60-123. Requirement for career counseling and other career-related
26 resources — Definition.
27 (a) As used in this section, "career-related resources" includes
28 without limitation information about:
29 (1) Available career and technical training; and
30 (2) Trade industries that provide employment opportunities.
31 (b) The Division of Higher Education shall maintain an accessible
32 location on its website with a link for career counseling and other career-
33 related resources that are available to students and provided by state-
34 supported institutions of higher education.
35 (c) A state-supported institution of higher education shall:
36 (1) Maintain on its website a link to the division's career
